<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06061072 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06061072 </ACCESS><LEADPARA>  Toyota Motor Corp. said today that it has bought a 40 percent stake in aMerrill Lynch andamp; Co. subsidiary in Tokyo. Toyota officials said their company,Japan's biggest automaker, acquired the share in Merrill Lynch InternationalCapital Management Co. through a subsidiary, Toyota Finance Corp., also ofTokyo. The price wasn't disclosed.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Business  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  TOYOTA BUYS STAKE IN MERRILL LYNCH UNIT  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Financial Digest  </MEMO><BYLINE>  Mercury News Staff and Wire Reports  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Stock Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  SAN JOSE MERCURY NEWS  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910301  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Friday  </DAY><MONTH>  March  </MONTH><PG.COL>  3D  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  55  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Friday March 1, 199100061072,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>